<p>New: ∅</p>
<p>Revised:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/vives/">Juan Luis Vives (Joannes Ludovicus Vives)</a> by Lorenzo Casini.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/scientific-reduction/">Scientific Reduction</a> by Raphael van Riel and Robert Van Gulick.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/models-science/">Models in Science</a> by Roman Frigg and Stephan Hartmann.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/quine-nf/">Quine’s New Foundations</a> by Thomas Forster.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/altruism-empirical/">Empirical Approaches to Altruism</a> by John Doris, Stephen Stich, Lachlan Walmsley, and Armin Schulz.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/structuralism-mathematics/">Structuralism in the Philosophy of Mathematics</a> by Erich Reck and Georg Schiemer.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/marcus-aurelius/">Marcus Aurelius</a> by Rachana Kamtekar.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/hegel-social-political/">Hegel’s Social and Political Philosophy</a> by Thom Brooks</li>
</ol>
